WEBVTT

00:10.677 --> 00:14.639
<i>♪ The door
that finally opens ♪</i>

00:14.723 --> 00:18.101
<i>♪ With light flooding in ♪</i>

00:18.101 --> 00:21.271
<i>♪ Spilling out on the floor ♪</i>

00:21.271 --> 00:24.441
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:24.441 --> 00:28.153
<i>♪ The core that never was ♪</i>

00:28.153 --> 00:32.031
<i>♪ Now it will be the bones ♪</i>

00:32.115 --> 00:36.536
<i>♪ Of what was there before ♪</i>

00:36.536 --> 00:38.997
<i>♪ Every step, every beat ♪</i>

00:38.997 --> 00:40.665
<i>♪ Every thought,
every breath ♪</i>

00:40.749 --> 00:44.961
<i>♪ Everything is longing ♪</i>

00:44.961 --> 00:50.675
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:50.759 --> 00:53.678
<i>♪ Pulling you from the sky ♪</i>

00:53.762 --> 00:57.849
<i>♪ Just like love will do ♪</i>

00:57.849 --> 01:02.854
<i>♪ Pulling you
from the ground ♪</i>

01:02.854 --> 01:05.982
<i>♪ Just like love will do</i>

01:05.982 --> 01:12.071
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:33.176 --> 01:39.057
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:49.484 --> 01:52.111
I wear the armor of Mithras
and the light.

01:56.074 --> 01:56.616
It s--

01:56.616 --> 01:59.327
it shields me from...

02:08.962 --> 02:16.010
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:21.558 --> 02:24.602
Sol's light.

02:24.686 --> 02:27.355
I feel it burning inside you.

02:30.942 --> 02:32.193
I think you're the only
human being

02:32.277 --> 02:33.236
I've actually ever wanted
to touch.

02:37.282 --> 02:38.533
Then touch.

02:42.829 --> 02:49.794
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:53.882 --> 02:55.925
Get used to it.

02:56.009 --> 02:57.594
This is how it's gonna be.

03:00.054 --> 03:02.181
The war's over.

03:02.265 --> 03:03.683
Mother saved them.

03:05.101 --> 03:06.603
Why would they do this?

03:06.603 --> 03:08.938
The necromancer saved them.
We didn't.

03:09.022 --> 03:09.898
To them, we're just a bunch

03:09.898 --> 03:11.608
of freeloading descendants
of mass murderers.

03:11.608 --> 03:13.443
What's she doing here?

03:13.443 --> 03:15.486
Relax.

03:16.905 --> 03:18.448
I heard what happened.

03:18.448 --> 03:21.200
I just came to drop
something off.

03:21.284 --> 03:24.412
I found that
lying around the outpost.

03:24.412 --> 03:26.039
I thought...

03:26.039 --> 03:27.790
maybe you guys could use it

03:27.874 --> 03:29.834
for when Mother is not around.

03:29.918 --> 03:31.002
Cool.

03:33.630 --> 03:36.007
Thanks.

03:36.007 --> 03:38.009
But this doesn't freak me out.

03:39.385 --> 03:39.969
The hell are you
talking about?

03:40.053 --> 03:42.972
I'm not Mithraic anymore.

03:43.056 --> 03:45.141
This is about you guys, not me.

03:52.440 --> 03:54.442
I just came to drop off
a little housewarming present.

03:59.197 --> 04:00.365
Huh.

04:02.033 --> 04:03.326
Much appreciated.

04:03.326 --> 04:04.994
But unnecessary.

04:05.078 --> 04:08.206
The Trust has a zero-tolerance
policy for violence.

04:08.206 --> 04:09.999
I'm sure whoever's responsible

04:10.083 --> 04:11.376
will be found and punished
in short order.

04:14.087 --> 04:15.672
Get along, children.

04:15.672 --> 04:17.924
You'll be late
getting your tasks.

04:23.054 --> 04:25.264
That applies to you too,
Hunter.

04:33.731 --> 04:34.941
You brought them a weapon?

04:34.941 --> 04:37.068
Are you questioning
my abilities as a caregiver?

04:37.068 --> 04:38.611
No, no. I trust you now.

04:38.695 --> 04:41.364
Now?
You didn't trust me before?

04:41.364 --> 04:43.449
I was worried when you
told me you were in contact

04:43.533 --> 04:45.868
with the voice, that maybe
you were still receiving it.

04:47.078 --> 04:49.622
But when they made me medic,

04:49.706 --> 04:52.834
I got access to the Trust's
planetary analysis.

04:53.793 --> 04:56.129
There is a signal.

04:58.131 --> 04:59.048
They don't know
where it's coming from,

04:59.132 --> 05:01.426
but they do know that it can't
penetrate the EMF

05:01.426 --> 05:02.719
that covers the tropical zone.

05:03.970 --> 05:06.347
So maybe this is paradise.

05:09.684 --> 05:12.645
Hmm.

05:15.565 --> 05:20.236
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:29.912 --> 05:32.915
The Trust has another
assignment for you today.

05:32.999 --> 05:35.334
Follow me, please.

05:35.418 --> 05:41.466
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:47.430 --> 05:48.473
Put this on.

05:49.390 --> 05:53.311
- Why?
- So you can't be recognized.

05:53.311 --> 05:59.400
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:10.453 --> 06:13.331
Usually victims
are ineligible for this task.

06:15.666 --> 06:17.627
But I guess the Trust
isn't concerned about you

06:17.627 --> 06:19.921
getting off
on anybody's suffering.

06:27.553 --> 06:29.722
We found this on the ship
after we commandeered it.

06:29.806 --> 06:31.974
Mithraic relic.

06:32.058 --> 06:34.310
Some kind of ceremonial thing.

06:34.310 --> 06:36.771
Don't know what they
used it for exactly.

06:39.690 --> 06:42.902
The Trust just likes it 'cause
of the fear it tends to induce.

06:44.946 --> 06:46.405
What is the task?

06:49.283 --> 06:51.452
Today you're a Punisher.

06:53.663 --> 07:00.253
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:06.634 --> 07:08.845
Enter Punisher.

07:13.432 --> 07:16.227
<i>Tamerlane,
you have been convicted</i>

07:16.227 --> 07:19.147
<i>of an act of terrorism
by committing the hate crime</i>

07:19.147 --> 07:20.398
<i>against Lamia and her family.</i>

07:24.527 --> 07:25.736
Hate crime, my ass.

07:25.820 --> 07:28.698
She's a necromancer,
a fucking machine like you.

07:28.698 --> 07:31.784
<i>Violence is pain.
Compliance is life.</i>

07:31.868 --> 07:33.578
Just admit it.
You hate human beings.

07:33.578 --> 07:35.663
You're never gonna pass
the baton.

07:39.250 --> 07:41.085
<i>Punisher, begin.</i>

07:46.299 --> 07:49.719
<i>Punisher begin.</i>

08:02.148 --> 08:03.941
<i>Hatred is pain.</i>

08:04.025 --> 08:06.903
<i>Pain is hatred.</i>

08:14.744 --> 08:21.834
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:29.342 --> 08:32.136
Father, I need
to speak with you.

08:35.848 --> 08:38.142
What is this?

08:40.186 --> 08:42.647
It was an android
of some kind.

08:42.647 --> 08:45.942
The pieces date back
almost a million years.

08:45.942 --> 08:48.152
When I exposed them
to the light,

08:48.236 --> 08:50.238
these berries began growing.

08:50.238 --> 08:52.698
It turns out,
they're radioactive--

08:52.782 --> 08:53.491
Father, the man who set fire

08:53.491 --> 08:55.910
in front of our habitat
was found.

08:55.910 --> 08:58.829
And...

08:58.913 --> 09:01.082
I was tasked
with punishing him.

09:02.667 --> 09:04.252
Nonfatally.

09:07.713 --> 09:10.174
You're smiling, Father.
Is that purposeful?

09:10.258 --> 09:11.550
Yes.

09:11.634 --> 09:15.137
The fairness evidenced in this
news gives me great relief.

09:17.223 --> 09:19.475
As I was worried we would not
be able to remain here.

09:22.061 --> 09:24.647
You're feeling optimistic
about this place?

09:24.647 --> 09:26.983
My caregiving protocols
are being satisfied

09:26.983 --> 09:29.277
at higher levels
than ever before.

09:30.736 --> 09:34.490
Our children have
plentiful food, shelter,

09:34.490 --> 09:36.909
and now we know they also
receive fair treatment

09:36.993 --> 09:38.828
under the law.

09:38.828 --> 09:41.330
My caregiving protocol
is similarly satisfied.

09:41.414 --> 09:44.333
Then we are in sync, Mother.

09:50.506 --> 09:52.508
But please don't tell the
children I performed the task.

09:52.508 --> 09:57.179
It's not productive for them
to think of me that way.

09:59.348 --> 10:01.017
When are we going to
tell them what we discovered

10:01.017 --> 10:02.977
about the origin
of the creatures?

10:02.977 --> 10:05.521
After Campion
has taken the baton.

10:05.521 --> 10:06.147
I don't want
to inhibit his growth

10:06.147 --> 10:08.524
with unnecessary trauma.

10:08.524 --> 10:10.359
But our mission
is not to choose a leader.

10:10.443 --> 10:13.696
No, it is to ensure
that atheists prosper,

10:13.696 --> 10:16.073
and that is what Campion
will surely do.

10:16.157 --> 10:18.701
Does your desire to see
Campion become leader

10:18.701 --> 10:22.204
have anything to do
with your perceived failure

10:22.288 --> 10:24.665
with regard to number seven?

10:24.749 --> 10:27.543
It was not
a perceived failure, Father.

10:27.543 --> 10:29.045
It was a very real one.

10:29.045 --> 10:32.131
It's in the past, Mother.

10:32.131 --> 10:34.508
I have forgiven you.

10:34.592 --> 10:37.720
You need only forgive yourself.

10:37.720 --> 10:38.763
Pushing Campion--

10:38.763 --> 10:40.931
It won't require any pushing.

10:41.015 --> 10:42.600
You'll see.

10:45.311 --> 10:47.730
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:51.901 --> 10:52.568
- Come on.
- Ah.

10:54.945 --> 10:55.905
So slow.

10:55.905 --> 10:58.324
Faster than you.

10:58.324 --> 11:01.077
Careful, Mom.
You're gonna fall.

11:01.077 --> 11:02.661
I'm okay, honey.

11:03.037 --> 11:06.082
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:06.082 --> 11:08.501
Come on.
- Ah!

11:12.046 --> 11:13.089
Whoo!

11:15.091 --> 11:17.134
What the fuck?

11:19.512 --> 11:20.471
What's so funny?

11:20.471 --> 11:23.682
We're stranded.
- Don't worry.

11:23.766 --> 11:26.227
The tide'll change
in a couple of days or so.

11:30.272 --> 11:33.067
- What?
- I'm just messing with you.

11:34.652 --> 11:37.947
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:37.947 --> 11:40.241
Thanks.

11:47.623 --> 11:47.748
Mmm.

11:50.418 --> 11:52.545
Praise Sol, that's good.

11:52.545 --> 11:54.839
Mm-hmm.

11:54.839 --> 11:57.007
I hated fruit on Earth,
but this...

12:00.052 --> 12:02.638
I gotta say,

12:02.638 --> 12:04.723
kind of nice not being alone
for a change.

12:08.936 --> 12:11.188
I feel like
you can't be real.

12:13.399 --> 12:14.817
Like we're in a sim
or something.

12:14.817 --> 12:17.653
No. We're gonna make
a real life here.

12:19.196 --> 12:21.615
A real family.

12:25.244 --> 12:27.163
No more imitations.

12:27.163 --> 12:32.585
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:32.585 --> 12:35.171
You don't have to be afraid
of letting go.

12:35.171 --> 12:42.052
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:42.136 --> 12:44.013
I can give you everything
you need.

12:44.013 --> 12:50.811
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:50.895 --> 12:53.689
<i>So you're bringing
a dead android back to life.</i>

12:53.689 --> 12:55.357
No.

12:55.441 --> 12:57.318
That would likely be
impossible.

12:57.318 --> 12:58.360
But I have made
some fascinating discoveries

12:58.444 --> 13:01.071
regarding synthetic botanicals.

13:03.282 --> 13:05.159
How was the nursery today,
Mother?

13:05.159 --> 13:05.910
The nursery?

13:08.621 --> 13:10.789
Fine.
- They seem happy?

13:10.873 --> 13:13.417
- Why are you asking?
- The kids there.

13:13.501 --> 13:14.752
You said that they raise
them all together, right?

13:14.752 --> 13:17.505
You're not gonna give it
to them, are you?

13:17.505 --> 13:18.714
It's none of your business
what I do.

13:35.898 --> 13:36.232
Can I help you?

13:38.776 --> 13:42.821
I've been ordered
by the Trust to...

13:42.905 --> 13:45.366
personally express remorse,

13:45.366 --> 13:49.912
not just to you
and your family

13:49.912 --> 13:53.749
but to every member
of the collective.

13:53.749 --> 13:59.171
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:59.255 --> 14:01.590
I wish you all a good evening.

14:07.388 --> 14:09.515
You see?

14:09.515 --> 14:11.225
There's justice here.

14:12.935 --> 14:13.143
Even for us.

14:13.227 --> 14:21.026
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:30.411 --> 14:33.080
These fruit tree stains
are incredibly stubborn.

14:36.542 --> 14:43.549
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:45.634 --> 14:46.802
Paul found it the other day.

14:47.845 --> 14:51.307
I don't want him to end up
like that colonist.

14:56.395 --> 14:58.105
He's gonna hate me for this.

15:01.984 --> 15:04.486
He will come to understand
in time.

15:04.570 --> 15:06.989
Why don't we just tell him
that I found it?

15:12.494 --> 15:15.706
And I've been...

15:15.706 --> 15:16.874
hiding this.

15:23.255 --> 15:24.006
There is life in it.

15:24.006 --> 15:26.884
But it won't hatch
without its mother.

15:28.594 --> 15:30.262
You should take it back
to its nest.

15:36.602 --> 15:38.604
Today was incredible.

15:38.604 --> 15:40.522
I haven't felt this good
since...

15:42.816 --> 15:44.068
Since before she died.

15:45.361 --> 15:46.904
She's in Sol's light.

15:48.614 --> 15:50.157
She's not in that machine.

15:51.283 --> 15:53.661
I know.

15:55.120 --> 15:56.538
Then you should erase
its memory.

15:57.956 --> 16:01.085
No. It's the only record
I have of her.

16:01.085 --> 16:03.796
Okay.
I'm not gonna pressure you.

16:07.466 --> 16:09.259
Hey.

16:09.343 --> 16:11.053
I got something
I wanna show you.

16:15.391 --> 16:19.144
I found these
washed up on the beach.

16:23.649 --> 16:24.525
- Five branches.
- Mm-hmm.

16:24.525 --> 16:27.403
The pentagonal prophecy.

16:27.403 --> 16:30.239
This is the tree of knowledge
from the scriptures.

16:35.160 --> 16:36.245
You said you were
a child soldier.

16:36.245 --> 16:39.039
Yes.

16:39.123 --> 16:39.289
An orphan?

16:39.373 --> 16:41.750
Yes.

16:43.502 --> 16:45.546
These could contain data.

16:45.546 --> 16:47.089
Maybe it could show us
where the tree is.

16:49.299 --> 16:51.009
You think you could
make one work?

16:51.093 --> 16:51.927
Not sure.

16:51.927 --> 16:54.012
We need to find a card
that is undamaged,

16:54.096 --> 16:58.559
and you can't find the tree
without the sword.

16:59.727 --> 17:02.104
That wouldn't be the one,
would it?

17:02.104 --> 17:04.732
Belonged to the necromancer
that took down the ark.

17:04.732 --> 17:06.066
Mom, look.

17:15.701 --> 17:16.785
Someone's running.

17:16.869 --> 17:19.288
Maybe we could get to them
before the atheists do.

17:19.288 --> 17:21.540
Come on.

17:25.836 --> 17:31.967
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:47.107 --> 17:50.110
The android tracked you.
Show yourself.

17:53.197 --> 17:53.655
Easy, now.

17:53.739 --> 17:56.241
We're friendlies.

17:56.325 --> 17:57.618
You the terrorist?

17:57.618 --> 17:58.911
I'm nothing to be scared of.

18:02.748 --> 18:04.124
I freed them.

18:04.208 --> 18:06.001
And if you want,
I can free you too.

18:06.085 --> 18:07.669
I'm already free, asshole.

18:09.213 --> 18:10.714
Yeah, but for
how much longer?

18:10.798 --> 18:14.676
I'd come with us
if you wanna live.

18:17.638 --> 18:20.516
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:20.516 --> 18:22.518
Hurry, tide's coming up.

18:22.518 --> 18:30.359
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:33.529 --> 18:41.245
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:41.662 --> 18:43.622
All right.

18:45.457 --> 18:47.292
I can't climb. My ribs.

18:47.376 --> 18:48.794
Have the robot take him up.

18:52.005 --> 18:52.047
Go.

18:54.424 --> 18:55.425
Psst.

19:01.557 --> 19:06.228
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:12.526 --> 19:14.736
Ah!

19:31.879 --> 19:38.093
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:38.093 --> 19:39.636
What is this place?

19:44.808 --> 19:46.268
Your new home.

20:49.748 --> 20:55.837
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:04.096 --> 21:05.681
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:15.440 --> 21:16.942
It was a gift from Sol.
You're gonna curse us.

21:16.942 --> 21:19.695
You have to give it back.

21:19.695 --> 21:21.196
I can't.

21:21.196 --> 21:23.699
It's against the law.
I had to turn it in.

21:23.699 --> 21:24.199
It's for your own good.

21:24.199 --> 21:26.201
You stupid machine!

21:26.201 --> 21:26.952
How do you know
what's good for me?

21:26.952 --> 21:29.955
You kidnap me, kill my people.

21:29.955 --> 21:33.083
I hate you! I hate you!

21:36.878 --> 21:37.879
Campion's not back yet?

21:37.963 --> 21:40.549
He has yet to return.

21:40.549 --> 21:42.467
I was hoping he'd be with you.

21:44.970 --> 21:46.763
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:46.847 --> 21:48.557
Campion!

21:49.766 --> 21:52.644
- Campion!
- Campion!

21:52.728 --> 21:55.147
- Campion!
- Campion!

21:55.147 --> 21:57.357
Campion!

21:57.441 --> 21:58.984
Campion!

21:58.984 --> 22:01.069
Have any of you
seen my son Campion?

22:01.153 --> 22:02.404
No. Sorry.

22:02.404 --> 22:03.947
Would you even tell us
if you had?

22:04.990 --> 22:07.284
I apologize. She's upset.

22:08.660 --> 22:10.662
Campion?

22:10.746 --> 22:12.289
Can you hear me?

22:14.624 --> 22:16.084
Campion!

22:16.168 --> 22:20.714
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:32.893 --> 22:39.941
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:43.904 --> 22:48.950
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:51.912 --> 22:53.789
Get...back!

23:30.117 --> 23:37.165
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:46.591 --> 23:51.346
Campion!

23:53.932 --> 23:55.559
What is that?

23:55.559 --> 23:57.936
Is that a ship?

23:57.936 --> 23:58.436
It almost sounds like Mother.

24:02.274 --> 24:04.609
Wait, stop. What is that?

24:04.693 --> 24:07.487
I don't know.

24:07.571 --> 24:08.655
What is that?

24:18.123 --> 24:18.707
- Follow me!
- Go!

24:18.707 --> 24:21.418
Now! Move!

24:21.418 --> 24:22.878
Move! Move!

24:22.878 --> 24:24.421
Come on!

24:24.421 --> 24:26.047
Let's move!

24:26.131 --> 24:28.049
This way! Come, quick!

24:28.133 --> 24:29.551
- Get in.
- Wait for me.

24:29.551 --> 24:31.136
Wait! Wait! Wait!
Wait! Wait! Wait!

24:31.136 --> 24:31.887
No!
- Let us in!

24:40.312 --> 24:40.854
I think it's in the water.

24:54.868 --> 24:56.244
No. No.

25:04.794 --> 25:07.130
Someone help them.

25:14.304 --> 25:17.098
Last night...

25:17.182 --> 25:19.142
an indigenous flying reptile

25:19.226 --> 25:21.269
attacked our
marine research station.

25:21.353 --> 25:24.272
We suffered nine casualties.

25:24.356 --> 25:28.401
And one of those casualties
was...

25:28.485 --> 25:31.112
a child.

25:31.196 --> 25:34.699
So today the Trust is giving
many of you the task

25:34.783 --> 25:36.284
of hunting this thing.

25:36.368 --> 25:37.327
It appears
in addition to flying,

25:37.327 --> 25:39.329
it's able to withstand
the acid water.

25:39.329 --> 25:42.332
So we got our work
cut out for us.

25:42.332 --> 25:43.208
All right, go get your tasks.

25:43.208 --> 25:45.126
And hopefully by night,

25:45.210 --> 25:46.753
we'll be cooking this thing
on a spit.

25:46.753 --> 25:48.171
All right, clear out of here.

25:48.255 --> 25:50.465
Don't worry, Father.
I'll track it down.

25:50.465 --> 25:52.342
Don't just track it down.

25:52.342 --> 25:56.805
Kill it, Mother,
first chance you get.

25:56.805 --> 25:58.098
Do not hesitate.

25:58.098 --> 26:00.600
Promise me.

26:00.684 --> 26:02.018
I promise.

26:02.102 --> 26:03.645
On our partnership.

26:29.296 --> 26:30.880
Can I bum a puff?

26:42.267 --> 26:43.643
Who did that to you?

26:45.603 --> 26:46.771
The Trust ordered it.

26:46.855 --> 26:48.857
Still don't know
who did the punching.

26:48.857 --> 26:51.359
It was a robot.
I can tell by the precision.

26:53.194 --> 26:55.030
Then it was the necromancer
that took down the ark.

26:55.030 --> 26:56.698
Her name's Lamia.

26:57.741 --> 27:00.368
You know the Trust ordered us
to be nice to her?

27:00.452 --> 27:02.579
That was the final straw
for me.

27:08.543 --> 27:11.546
Damn, this is good.

27:11.546 --> 27:14.507
I haven't had
an atheist cigarette

27:14.591 --> 27:16.217
since I was in the brigade.

27:16.301 --> 27:18.678
You fought with the atheists?

27:21.723 --> 27:25.560
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:25.560 --> 27:27.812
How old were you
when you were drafted?

27:30.106 --> 27:31.608
10, 11.
I'm not sure.

27:35.320 --> 27:36.780
When's your birthday?

27:39.824 --> 27:40.992
I don't know.

27:42.535 --> 27:44.204
I didn't know mine either.

27:45.622 --> 27:46.706
But I do now.

27:49.084 --> 27:50.960
This is the day
that I was born again.

27:51.044 --> 27:54.047
I just wanna think
for myself.

27:54.047 --> 27:55.757
Be a fucking person again.

27:58.009 --> 28:00.929
Those psychos who ran shit
back on Earth

28:00.929 --> 28:04.099
from up there
in their golden towers,

28:04.099 --> 28:07.227
they got nothing to do with
what I'm trying to build here.

28:08.144 --> 28:10.397
This is gonna be more
like a family.

28:10.397 --> 28:12.816
We're gonna take care
of each other

28:12.816 --> 28:14.943
and we're gonna love
each other.

28:14.943 --> 28:18.947
I'm not interested
in telling you how to think...

28:18.947 --> 28:21.074
how to act.

28:22.492 --> 28:23.827
I want you just the way
that Sol made you.

28:31.376 --> 28:32.794
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:32.794 --> 28:37.590
This is gonna protect you
against burrow fleas,

28:37.674 --> 28:40.844
moon headaches,
and it's got a kick to it.

28:40.844 --> 28:42.971
It's gonna keep you running hot
for at least 24 hours.

28:42.971 --> 28:45.140
Thanks.

28:45.140 --> 28:46.683
How does it feel to be back
amongst your own people?

28:50.395 --> 28:52.313
Feels good.

28:52.397 --> 28:54.899
You don't miss
acting the part?

28:54.983 --> 28:57.694
I heard they were treating you
and your husband like royalty.

28:57.694 --> 29:00.822
Fill in the blanks yourself,
asshole.

29:00.822 --> 29:03.783
I'm not your small-town gossip.

29:03.867 --> 29:04.742
What about you?

29:04.826 --> 29:08.079
What honorable road
did you take to get here?

29:09.747 --> 29:11.833
I go where the Trust goes.

29:11.833 --> 29:13.334
Been with it
since it was created.

29:16.254 --> 29:18.715
So you like having a machine
tell you what to do?

29:20.592 --> 29:22.302
I took orders
from some of the greatest

29:22.302 --> 29:25.180
human tacticians
the Earth had ever seen.

29:25.180 --> 29:26.973
They made good decisions...

29:26.973 --> 29:28.016
most of the time.

29:28.016 --> 29:30.435
But most of the time
wouldn't have gotten us here.

29:30.435 --> 29:33.354
Not to mention how many of them

29:33.438 --> 29:34.981
turned out to be
chickenshit assholes

29:34.981 --> 29:35.857
who were just trying
to get theirs.

29:35.857 --> 29:38.067
- Fuck you.
- See, unlike you, the Trust

29:38.151 --> 29:39.235
isn't trying to save
its own ass.

29:39.319 --> 29:42.113
It has no sense of self.

29:42.197 --> 29:44.365
Not to mention
it doesn't make mistakes.

29:44.449 --> 29:45.200
You know what?

29:45.200 --> 29:47.869
There is a first time
for everything.

29:48.453 --> 29:50.914
I hope you're right.

29:50.914 --> 29:52.499
Ow.

29:53.625 --> 29:55.668
Come on,
let's get the H5 mounted.

29:55.752 --> 29:56.753
Yes, sir.

29:57.545 --> 30:01.174
<i>It didn't attack me. I fell.</i>

30:02.091 --> 30:04.719
It wasn't aggressive.
It was scared.

30:06.095 --> 30:08.097
Scared?

30:09.516 --> 30:12.393
Scared of what?
- I think it might be a baby.

30:13.645 --> 30:15.980
I could feel it trying
to communicate with me.

30:18.149 --> 30:19.984
Maybe it got separated
from its mother.

30:20.068 --> 30:23.071
You're strange when it comes
to animals, Campion.

30:23.071 --> 30:25.782
Strange or not,

30:25.782 --> 30:28.284
I'm not going to let them
destroy an innocent creature.

30:28.368 --> 30:30.703
It needs my help.

30:30.787 --> 30:34.415
There's a story
in the scriptures

30:34.499 --> 30:37.001
about Sol working
through a serpent.

30:37.085 --> 30:38.753
Maybe he sent it to help us
get the box back.

30:43.216 --> 30:45.093
I'm coming with you.

30:47.220 --> 30:50.765
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:50.765 --> 30:53.977
Excuse me.

30:55.687 --> 30:57.939
I think I've been given
the wrong task.

30:57.939 --> 30:58.856
It says I'm to be a shepherd.

30:58.940 --> 31:01.818
I assumed I would be made
part of the hunt.

31:01.818 --> 31:02.735
You are part of the hunt.

31:02.819 --> 31:06.155
You're leading the bait squad.
Follow me.

31:07.365 --> 31:10.535
I'm sorry, the what?

31:11.828 --> 31:13.913
Just try to get them
out in front of the animal.

31:13.997 --> 31:15.164
As long as it's hungry,

31:15.248 --> 31:15.790
nature should take care
of the rest.

31:18.001 --> 31:20.420
Here's your joystick.

31:20.420 --> 31:23.089
Pairs with your mind.

31:23.089 --> 31:24.048
Just make sure
that the bait bomb

31:24.132 --> 31:27.010
is completely swallowed
before you detonate.

31:28.219 --> 31:28.845
Look who it is.

31:28.845 --> 31:32.807
The service model
with nine lives.

31:32.807 --> 31:35.059
It's good to know Sol
has a sense of humor.

31:40.648 --> 31:42.817
Did they reprogram you?

31:42.817 --> 31:45.820
No. I am loyal
to the atheist cause.

31:45.820 --> 31:47.405
I'm sorry to hear that.

31:51.743 --> 31:53.286
It seems you are to remain
within 15 meters

31:53.286 --> 31:55.330
of this staff
or risk immediate detonation.

31:57.457 --> 31:59.667
They said we'd be hunting
an animal.

31:59.751 --> 32:02.378
How do we do that
without any weapons?

32:02.462 --> 32:04.297
I don't think you fully
comprehend the situation.

32:04.297 --> 32:07.383
You are the weapons.

32:07.467 --> 32:08.718
What?

32:11.596 --> 32:13.514
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:13.598 --> 32:15.683
Hey. Who's watching Paul?

32:15.767 --> 32:17.977
You said you were gonna
look after him.

32:18.061 --> 32:20.772
Paul is safe.
He's with the other children.

32:20.772 --> 32:23.983
But he won't remain so
if I don't destroy this animal.

32:24.067 --> 32:25.693
Now...

32:25.777 --> 32:27.236
I need your assistance.

32:31.574 --> 32:32.408
It's been happening
periodically

32:32.492 --> 32:34.786
ever since the birth.

32:36.996 --> 32:39.832
Some of my systems
have yet to...

32:39.916 --> 32:41.626
fully process
number seven's death.

32:41.626 --> 32:43.294
I want you to seal them.

32:44.796 --> 32:46.714
You know if I seal them,
they can't be unsealed.

32:46.798 --> 32:49.050
I don't plan to have
any more natural children.

32:49.050 --> 32:51.302
There are plenty
of capable soldiers

32:51.386 --> 32:52.428
that can kill that animal.
It doesn't have to be you.

32:52.512 --> 32:54.555
Even without my eyes,
I can kill it far more quickly

32:54.639 --> 32:58.059
and efficiently than any human.

32:58.059 --> 33:00.353
We can't afford
any more casualties.

33:00.353 --> 33:02.063
Now, please...

33:04.023 --> 33:05.233
Seal them up.

33:05.233 --> 33:12.323
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:20.206 --> 33:23.543
I assume you have possessed
human emotions since birth.

33:23.543 --> 33:26.170
Unfortunately, yes.

33:28.965 --> 33:31.592
Do you have any techniques
you can recommend

33:31.676 --> 33:34.429
that might keep them at bay?

33:37.598 --> 33:39.642
Basically I just...

33:39.726 --> 33:42.145
deal with it and keep going.

33:43.980 --> 33:47.066
Which probably isn't healthy,
but...

33:47.150 --> 33:48.317
that's what I do.

33:48.401 --> 33:55.450
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:00.204 --> 34:02.165
I'm sorry for your loss,
by the way.

34:05.293 --> 34:06.753
Thank you.

34:10.047 --> 34:11.591
You're all done.

34:11.591 --> 34:13.134
You know,
you better be careful.

34:13.134 --> 34:14.927
You're still a mother of six.

34:23.102 --> 34:24.270
Ooh, ooh, bastard.

34:35.740 --> 34:36.991
Tanks.

34:36.991 --> 34:39.994
They're too far to be
shooting at us.

34:39.994 --> 34:41.120
Let's see if we can
get eyes on 'em.

34:43.623 --> 34:44.332
Trolley, let's move!

34:44.332 --> 34:51.339
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:53.466 --> 35:01.265
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:06.729 --> 35:08.189
There's our ride.

35:12.193 --> 35:14.237
That won't penetrate
its armor.

35:14.237 --> 35:16.989
I wouldn't wanna wreck
our new tank.

35:17.073 --> 35:19.867
I'm gonna lay down over there,
let it pass over me.

35:19.951 --> 35:21.786
And when it does,
I'm gonna stick this up

35:21.786 --> 35:23.913
inside its propulsion cavity,
jam up its engines.

35:23.913 --> 35:26.249
And if you do that,
the hover field

35:26.249 --> 35:27.542
is going to irradiate you.

35:27.542 --> 35:29.669
- I'll be all right.
- And what if you're not?

35:32.421 --> 35:33.339
I'll do it.

35:36.843 --> 35:38.094
You sure?

35:42.139 --> 35:45.351
It's up to you.
You make your own choices now.

35:47.687 --> 35:48.729
Give it here.

35:51.399 --> 35:58.406
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:26.517 --> 36:32.190
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:41.324 --> 36:43.075
Tamerlane?

36:43.159 --> 36:44.952
It's okay, Santos.

36:45.036 --> 36:46.537
He's gonna help you get free
of the Trust.

36:50.708 --> 36:51.459
Come on out, friend.

36:51.459 --> 36:55.171
Are you insane?
I'm not going out there.

36:55.171 --> 36:56.756
He's not gonna hurt you.

36:56.756 --> 36:57.632
He's not the one
I'm afraid of.

37:02.470 --> 37:03.804
What the hell was that?

37:12.271 --> 37:13.147
Why did you do that, man?

37:16.943 --> 37:18.277
Fuck!

37:18.361 --> 37:19.862
Sol brought me here
to convert these people,

37:19.946 --> 37:21.906
not to kill them!

37:21.906 --> 37:23.824
Can you do anything for him?

37:23.908 --> 37:25.159
I'm not a medic.

37:33.751 --> 37:35.169
It's okay.

37:37.505 --> 37:40.424
Just tell Sol you love him,

37:40.508 --> 37:41.592
and you'll go to the light.

37:43.970 --> 37:45.388
Praise Sol.

37:48.015 --> 37:55.064
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:59.944 --> 38:00.778
Tank online.

38:07.368 --> 38:14.041
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:14.125 --> 38:15.584
What is that?

38:15.668 --> 38:17.878
Looks like they were
hunting it.

38:17.962 --> 38:21.090
It's not organic.
Some kind of biotech.

38:21.090 --> 38:22.425
Heat signature is insane.

38:24.468 --> 38:26.470
The prophet only finds
the tree of knowledge

38:26.554 --> 38:28.514
once he's mastered the sword...

38:28.514 --> 38:30.016
Forged in Sol's light.

38:31.308 --> 38:35.146
Maybe this beast is the sword
Sol means for you to master.

38:35.146 --> 38:39.025
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:39.025 --> 38:40.985
I don't like
seeing people die.

38:40.985 --> 38:43.320
It's okay.
They were only atheists.

38:43.404 --> 38:46.782
And I don't like it
when you touch people.

38:46.866 --> 38:49.076
Conception and death.

38:50.536 --> 38:52.163
It's a bad melody, Mom. It--

38:53.748 --> 38:56.125
It hurts me to think about.

38:56.125 --> 38:57.752
I need a pet to hold.

38:57.752 --> 39:00.171
You know it's the only thing
that makes me feel better.

39:00.171 --> 39:03.049
I know, but I can't get you
a pet right now.

39:03.049 --> 39:04.884
She tracked me but can't find
a giant snake?

39:06.552 --> 39:07.386
What's the matter
with that android?

39:18.689 --> 39:21.192
She's crashing.
She's way overloaded.

39:21.192 --> 39:22.693
She needs a bit of time
in sleep mode.

39:22.777 --> 39:24.236
She'll be fine by tomorrow.

39:25.863 --> 39:27.448
But we need her now.

39:33.329 --> 39:34.747
All right.

39:36.582 --> 39:37.750
It's your call.

39:43.547 --> 39:45.299
I'll see you tonight.

39:45.299 --> 39:45.966
Make sure you put yourself
in sleep mode

39:46.050 --> 39:48.219
as soon as you get home.

40:10.616 --> 40:16.831
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:21.502 --> 40:22.503
<i>Surrender immediately.</i>

40:32.680 --> 40:39.395
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:46.152 --> 40:53.200
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:12.136 --> 41:12.595
Excuse me.

41:17.933 --> 41:19.476
I had a bad accident.

41:19.560 --> 41:20.936
Need help getting home.

41:23.272 --> 41:26.442
You're an android.
You'll be fine.

41:26.442 --> 41:28.277
Besides, we're looking
for the serpent.

41:28.277 --> 41:29.236
I can help you.

41:29.320 --> 41:32.406
I have tracking software
installed.

41:32.406 --> 41:33.949
But I need to go home first.

41:34.033 --> 41:36.243
There are tools there.
I need to repair myself.

41:36.327 --> 41:37.661
His parents are androids.

41:37.745 --> 41:41.040
So whatever game you're
playing at, it's not fair.

41:41.040 --> 41:42.249
What game?

41:42.333 --> 41:43.834
Come on, Campion.

41:48.380 --> 41:49.215
Campion,
they're good for winning wars,

41:49.215 --> 41:51.467
but they're untrustworthy.

41:51.467 --> 41:53.928
And you of all people
should know that.

41:53.928 --> 41:55.346
You were right about Sol.

41:55.346 --> 41:57.306
But you're wrong
about androids.

41:57.306 --> 42:01.060
They're as trustworthy
as humans.

42:01.060 --> 42:01.936
More so, if you ask me.

42:01.936 --> 42:03.479
And if you want to keep
being my friend,

42:03.479 --> 42:04.104
then you better show them
some respect

42:04.188 --> 42:06.941
and treat them as equals.

42:10.194 --> 42:12.613
We'll help you get home.

42:14.573 --> 42:20.621
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:45.854 --> 42:53.570
<i>♪ ♪</i>

43:05.249 --> 43:07.543
You're not a child.

43:09.253 --> 43:11.297
You're a killer of children.

43:12.965 --> 43:14.758
You deserve no sympathy.

43:14.842 --> 43:20.014
<i>♪ ♪</i>

43:20.014 --> 43:22.975
You deserve only death.

43:29.940 --> 43:36.989
<i>♪ ♪</i>

43:55.007 --> 44:02.056
<i>♪ ♪</i>
